Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:43.84,English,,0,0,0,,but judging by our results.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:43.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:45.35,English,,0,0,0,,This was not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:45.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.35,0:04:49.47,English,,0,0,0,,- The rotor wash doesn't extend down below the helicopter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.35,0:04:49.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:53.70,English,,0,0,0,,all that far. It dissipates pretty quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:53.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:05:00.10,English,,0,0,0,,- So, you can consider the air resistance on the rope as entirely due to its motion through still air.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:05:00.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:03.81,English,,0,0,0,,Imagine dividing the rope up into many short sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:03.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.81,0:05:09.11,English,,0,0,0,,Each section has the same weight and experiences the same amount of air resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.81,0:05:09.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:10.98,English,,0,0,0,,because it has the same cross-sectional area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:10.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.98,0:05:13.23,English,,0,0,0,,And it's moving at the same speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.98,0:05:13.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:15.64,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the tension in any section of the rope
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:15.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,must balance the sum of the air resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:18.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:21.48,English,,0,0,0,,and weight of all the sections beneath it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:21.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:24.72,English,,0,0,0,,So, the tension is zero at the bottom of the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.16,English,,0,0,0,,and it increases linearly up to a maximum at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:33.09,English,,0,0,0,,You can see the tension is small at the bottom of the rope, and that's why it wiggles around
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:33.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.09,0:05:35.36,English,,0,0,0,,while the top is much steadier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.09,0:05:35.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.36,0:05:37.71,English,,0,0,0,,Now, although the magnitude of tension changes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.36,0:05:37.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.71,0:05:40.65,English,,0,0,0,,throughout the rope, it's direction doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.71,0:05:40.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:43.38,English,,0,0,0,,And that's because the ratio of air resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:43.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:47.68,English,,0,0,0,,to weight is the same at every point along the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:47.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:52.54,English,,0,0,0,,That is why a uniform flexible cable hangs in a straight diagonal line
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:52.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.54,0:05:56.06,English,,0,0,0,,when pulled at constant speed by a helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.54,0:05:56.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.06,0:05:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,If the helicopter flies faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.06,0:05:57.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.86,0:06:02.66,English,,0,0,0,,the angle of the rope changes, but it still makes a diagonal straight line
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.86,0:06:02.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:05.74,English,,0,0,0,,because the ratio of air resistance to weight
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:05.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,is still constant along the entire length of the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:09.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:14.97,English,,0,0,0,,But this got me wondering, "What would happen if we added a weight
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:14.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.97,0:06:16.26,English,,0,0,0,,to the end of the rope?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.97,0:06:16.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:20.47,English,,0,0,0,,Here, I have a 20 pound, that's an eight or nine kilos kettlebell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:20.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:22.32,English,,0,0,0,,And I want to ask you to make a prediction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:22.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:25.32,English,,0,0,0,,What shape do you think the rope will make now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:25.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.49,English,,0,0,0,,Will it still be that diagonal,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:31.33,English,,0,0,0,,or will it be one of the other five options?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:31.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.33,0:06:32.40,English,,0,0,0,,One more question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.33,0:06:32.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.40,0:06:34.25,English,,0,0,0,,If we chucked a weight at the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.40,0:06:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.18,0:06:36.52,English,,0,0,0,,which shape would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.18,0:06:36.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:37.65,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh. - Probably D.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:37.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.14,0:06:42.35,English,,0,0,0,,- B, or possibly C.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.14,0:06:42.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:43.29,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Does that change it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:43.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:44.82,English,,0,0,0,,- Then I think it would be B.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:44.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.60,0:06:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,- Easy to do on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.60,0:06:49.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, we're dropping the rope over the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:56.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:07:00.42,English,,0,0,0,,This one has 20 pound kettlebell off the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:07:00.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:05.25,English,,0,0,0,,How's that feel when it's dangling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:05.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.25,0:07:07.46,English,,0,0,0,,- No lateral displacement at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.25,0:07:07.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:08.41,English,,0,0,0,,- Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:08.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.41,0:07:09.92,English,,0,0,0,,- How's your forearms doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.41,0:07:09.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:11.14,English,,0,0,0,,- I'm feeling good, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:11.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:14.35,English,,0,0,0,,I feel like this is the easy way, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:14.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:16.60,English,,0,0,0,,Gonna feel different when I gotta pull it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:16.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:19.10,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay, is it down? - Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:19.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's give it a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:21.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.17,0:07:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,Here the helicopter is flying at nearly a hundred kilometers per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.17,0:07:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.16,0:07:31.59,English,,0,0,0,,and the rope makes a different shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.16,0:07:31.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:39.20,English,,0,0,0,,You can clearly see, it looks like an inverted J.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:39.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.20,0:07:41.59,English,,0,0,0,,This is option D.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.20,0:07:41.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:45.64,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, this is how the question on the qualifying exam originated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:45.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.64,0:07:48.79,English,,0,0,0,,- So, I taught for a semester in Hong Kong,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.64,0:07:48.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:51.61,English,,0,0,0,,and we'd go hiking in the new territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:51.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,One of the times I was hiking,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:53.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:56.76,English,,0,0,0,,I saw a helicopter fly with a cable beneath it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:56.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:07:59.77,English,,0,0,0,,It was carrying something to one of the remote parts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:07:59.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.77,0:08:01.83,English,,0,0,0,,of the Hong Kong new territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.77,0:08:01.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,And I saw the shape of the cable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:03.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:07.82,English,,0,0,0,,and thought to myself , "That looks a little counter intuitive and very neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:07.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,This might make a good multiple choice question
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:10.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:13.94,English,,0,0,0,,for the selection exam for the students."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:17.29,English,,0,0,0,,The cable that I saw had a weight hanging on the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:17.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,which gave it a certain curved shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:19.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.78,0:08:22.74,English,,0,0,0,,When I shared this with the other coaches, another coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.78,0:08:22.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.74,0:08:25.15,English,,0,0,0,,Andrew Linn , looked at it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.74,0:08:25.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:28.78,English,,0,0,0,,and said , "I think the question might even be more fun
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:28.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:31.18,English,,0,0,0,,if there is no weight on the cable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:31.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.18,0:08:34.25,English,,0,0,0,,because that is even harder to imagine."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.18,0:08:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.55,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] To understand why the rope makes this shape,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,we can use the same analysis as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:40.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:44.33,English,,0,0,0,,But now we need to add a large weight to the end of the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:44.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:48.23,English,,0,0,0,,And this means at the bottom, the tension needs to be almost vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:48.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.23,0:08:50.44,English,,0,0,0,,to support the weight of the kettlebell,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.23,0:08:50.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.44,0:08:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,which has a lot of weight but not much air resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.44,0:08:53.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:57.83,English,,0,0,0,,As you go up the rope, the ratio of total air resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:57.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:01.75,English,,0,0,0,,to weight for everything beneath increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:01.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:05.00,English,,0,0,0,,So, the rope turns more horizontal in order for the tension
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:05.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:08.23,English,,0,0,0,,to balance out that increasing air resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:08.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,- You're more than halfway. You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:14.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:16.04,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] For the final test,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:16.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] 对于最后的测试
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.04,0:09:21.83,English,,0,0,0,,I wanted to add something to the bottom of the rope that added almost no weight, but significant air resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.04,0:09:21.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想在绳子的底部加上一个几乎没有什么重量，但对空气阻力很敏感的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:25.40,English,,0,0,0,,So, I picked a Veritasium flag, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:25.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以当然，我拿了一个真理元素的旗子
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.40,0:09:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think about hanging this at the end of the rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.40,0:09:28.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，你觉得这条绳子的尾端会发生什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.26,0:09:30.39,English,,0,0,0,,- Well, it's all science experiment for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:33.65,English,,0,0,0,,'cause these are all the things you'd never do with a helicopter in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.26,0:09:33.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 对于我来说这些都是些科学研究，因为你搞的这些试验都是在实际操作中不会做出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:37.34,English,,0,0,0,,- What would it be the real risks, like tail rotor or this rotor, or both?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:37.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 做这些动作，真正的风险在哪里？是在尾部的马达还是这个马达还是都是？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:38.26,English,,0,0,0,,- Either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:38.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 都是。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:40.85,English,,0,0,0,,Any kind of this getting into the inner tail rotor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.85,0:09:43.38,English,,0,0,0,,would be destruction to the aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:43.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,任何这种东西如果跑到了尾部马达里面，那这飞机就无了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:03.23,English,,0,0,0,,And we 'll start,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:03.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们开始吧
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.23,0:10:04.69,English,,0,0,0,, here we go .
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.23,0:10:04.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,走
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:13.99,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Now the rope still seems to be pretty straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:13.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] 现在这绳子看起来还是停止的诶
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.99,0:10:15.68,English,,0,0,0,,I think it's because the flag
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.68,0:10:17.92,English,,0,0,0,,isn't actually adding much drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.99,0:10:17.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想这是因为这旗子还不会（对绳子）增加很足够的拉力的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:21.35,English,,0,0,0,,Still looks pretty crazy, interestingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:21.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但有意思的是，这还是看起来挺疯狂的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.35,0:10:26.63,English,,0,0,0,,So, we decided to add a small parachute to the end of the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.35,0:10:26.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，我们决定去在绳子的尾端加一个小得降落伞
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.63,0:10:28.61,English,,0,0,0,,All right, let's try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.63,0:10:28.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好了，我们来试一下
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.61,0:10:30.46,English,,0,0,0,,The concern here was that the parachute
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.46,0:10:33.21,English,,0,0,0,,could get flipped up into the rotors during deployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.61,0:10:33.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样做的风险就是这个小降落伞有可能在部署的时候滑到马达里面
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:36.17,English,,0,0,0,,So, we bundled the shoot up into a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:36.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，我们将这个伞打包了起来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.38,English,,0,0,0,,- [Craig] Very nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Craig] 做得很棒
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.38,0:10:43.07,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Does it deploy more than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.38,0:10:43.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] 这样做有让拉力增加吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.07,0:10:44.87,English,,0,0,0,,- [Craig] No, but once we start moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:47.21,English,,0,0,0,,its gonna grab a lot of air.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.07,0:10:47.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Craig] 没有，但是一旦我们开始移动，它就将抓住很多的空气
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.61,English,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] Now, with the parachute at the end of the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- [Derek] 现在，我们在绳子尾部加了个降落伞之后
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:55.89,English,,0,0,0,,it makes a J shape, which is answer C.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:55.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绳子就变成了J形，也就是答案C的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.94,0:10:59.53,English,,0,0,0,,With extra air resistance at the end of the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.94,0:10:59.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着更多的空气阻力加在绳子的尾端
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.53,0:11:03.62,English,,0,0,0,,but not much weight, the tension has to be virtually horizontal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.53,0:11:03.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但（因为在这个点）重力并不是很大 ，（绳子的）张力方向就需要相当接近水平方向
